Gov. AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq of Kwara has appointed seven new Special Advisers (SAs). This is contained in a statement by Mr Rafiu Ajakaye, his Chief Press Secretary on Friday in Ilorin. Ajakaye named some of the appointees to include Mr Bashir Adigun, a reporter with Channel TV, who was appointed SA political communications. He said others included retired Brig-Gen. Saliu Bello SA security; Prof. Adekunle Dunmade SA health; Mr Ahmed Aluko SA special duties and Mr Attahiru Ibrahim SA youths and sports.(NAN) 